Sensex Index Plunges Below 16,000 for First Time Since May 2010 in Mumbai

-- B y   S h i k h a r   B a l w a n i
-- 
2011-08-19T08:51:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/sensex-index-plunges-below-16-000-for-first-time-since-may-2010-in-mumbai.html
India ’s Bombay Stock Exchange
Sensitive Index, or Sensex, slid below 16,000 for the first time
since May 2010 in Mumbai trading today. The gauge retreated 2.9
percent to 15,988.99 at 2:19 p.m. local time. The S&P CNX Nifty
index dropped 2.9 percent to 4,799.90. Infosys Ltd., the
nation’s second-largest software services provider, plunged 7.5
percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shikhar Balwani in Mumbai at 
 sbalwani@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
